@startuml
title Viaverse Worker Onboarding — Sequence Diagram

actor Worker
participant "KMP / Web Client" as Client
participant "API Gateway / App BFF" as BFF
participant "identity-service" as Identity
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
participant "media-service" as Media
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka
participant "search-service" as Search

Worker -> Client : enable Work Mode
Client -> BFF : POST /work/onboarding/start
BFF -> Identity : check capability eligibility
Identity -> DB : load AccountCapability
Identity --> BFF : allowed / blocked

BFF -> Marketplace : create WorkerProfile draft
Marketplace -> DB : insert WorkerProfile(DRAFT)

Worker -> Client : categories / area / availability
Client -> BFF : PATCH worker profile
BFF -> Marketplace : updateWorkerProfile
Marketplace -> DB : persist categories/area/availability

Worker -> Client : optional portfolio media
Client -> BFF : POST /media/upload-sessions
BFF -> Media : createUploadSession
Media -> DB : store MediaAsset
Media --> Client : presigned upload URL

Worker -> Client : publish profile
Client -> BFF : POST /work/profile/publish
BFF -> Marketplace : publishWorkerProfile
Marketplace -> DB : set ACTIVE + insert outbox
Marketplace -> Kafka : WorkerProfileActivated
Kafka -> Search : index public worker profile

note bottom
Worker profile activation publishes search/matching projections.
Profile source-of-truth remains marketplace-service/PostgreSQL.
end note
@enduml
